    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Joannes Ponderius (Binche, 10 November
                    1532)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">He has seen Hans Katzianer’s letter to King Ferdinand I,
                            according to which Andrea Gritti and King John I, once they heard that
                            he was going there with his army, at once retreated from Esztergom and
                            fled. Gritti entrusted Buda to his son with 100 horsemen and 400
                            infantrymen, which would thus have been easy to capture, but the Tirol
                            infantrymen turned back from Esztergom, saying that their contract has
                            expired; while Katzianer only has 1,500 infantrymen, which is not enough
                            to capture Buda.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="15321110_1_1.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad Ioannem Ponderium.<note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">We do not
                        know him more closely.</note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Exemplum litterarum <persName>Ioannis Kachyanes</persName>,<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Hans Katzianer.</note> quas ad regem dedit
                        <persName>Ferdinandum</persName>, vidimus hodie, quae significabat
                        <persName>Ioannem</persName> vaivodam et <persName>Andream
                        Gritti</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.3">Sometimes Oláh writes
                        “Andrea” instead of “Ludovico”, see Ep. 244. Note 7., and Ep. 283. Note
                            4.<ref>olahus.tei.15320728_1</ref></note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15321004_1</ref><placeName>Strigonium</placeName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.4">Esztergom.</note> obsidentes<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.5">See Ep.
                        283.<ref>olahus.tei.15321004_1</ref></note> audita ipsius <persName>Ioannis
                        Kochyaner</persName> cum exercitu istuc profectione statim </p>
                <pb facs="15321110_1_2.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.3">obsidionem solvisse et aufugisse. <placeName>Budae</placeName> vero
                    relictum <persName>filium</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.6">Ludovico
                        Gritti.</note> ipsius <persName>Gritti</persName> cum ducentis equitibus ac
                    quadringentis peditibus. Quodsi ita est, non ita quidem esset magni laboris
                        <placeName>Budam</placeName> ab illis recuperare, sed nostri milites
                    Tirolenses, statim cum pervenissent <placeName>Strigonium</placeName>, usque
                    domum sunt reversi, allegantes tempus militiae eorum praeteriisse. Quamobrem
                        <persName>Kochyaner</persName> mille et quingentos saltem dicitur habere
                    pedites et aliquot ex nostris husaronibus, qui soli difficulter
                        <placeName>Budam</placeName> recuperabunt. Vale.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Binsii</placeName> 10. Novembris 1532.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
